---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>Prove what your agents did.</h1>
    <p class="tagline">
      <strong>ponens</strong> turns an AI agent's session into a higher-level
      <strong>reasoning record</strong> — a curated, verifiable account of <em>what it built and
      why</em> — then makes the reasoning rigorous and governs it with
      <strong>Computable Governance</strong>: machine-checkable best-practice policies.
    </p>
    <div class="cta">
      <code>pip install ponens</code>
      <a class="btn" href="/gallery">Browse the policy gallery →</a>
    </div>
    <p class="etymology">
      From <em>modus ponens</em> — the rule of inference <code>P → Q, P ⊢ Q</code>.
      Given the policies and the recorded work, ponens derives whether the reasoning holds.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <article>
      <h3>Author traces</h3>
      <p>Record an agent's reasoning as a typed, immutable trace — actions, artifacts, lineage, proofs.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Computable Governance</h3>
      <p>Policies are machine-checkable rules over the trace — conformance checking (temporal logic over finite traces, à la process mining) brought to AI agents. A real gate, run offline.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Pull from the gallery</h3>
      <p>A community gallery of versioned, content-hashed policies — <code>ponens policies search</code> and add them to a trace.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <h3>Bind to commits &amp; sync</h3>
      <p>Bind a trace 1:1 to a git commit and push to a hub backend for review, snapshots, and audit.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="quickstart">
    <h2>Quickstart</h2>
    <pre><code>ponens registry update
ponens policies search payments

ponens policies add tests_before_commit --into ./trace.json
ponens trace check ./trace.json

ponens bind &amp;&amp; ponens push</code></pre>
  </section>
</Layout>
